Introduction

Choi Hyo-jung is a South Korean singer signed with WM Entertainment. She is the leader and lead vocalist of the girl group OH MY GIRL and its sub-unit OH MY GIRL BANHANA.

She only trained under the company for 6 months before making her official debut in the group.

On April 20, 2015, she debuted as a member of OH MY GIRL with the group’s self-titled debut mini album. She also joined the group’s special sub-unit, OH MY GIRL BANHANA, with the special album Banana Allergy Monkey on April 2, 2018.
